13
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:55,620
You may have already used chatbots before and realized that you can ask it for information,

14
00:00:56,180 --> 00:00:57,160
like with a search engine.

15
00:00:57,280 --> 00:01:03,780
There's actually quite a lot that you can do with chatbots, so I would like to group these types of tasks into seven categories.

16
00:01:04,379 --> 00:01:18,680
You can expand, you can synthesize, you can transform, evaluate, you can chat, take actions, and you can also input not just text, but also images with text into the chatbot.

17
00:01:18,820 --> 00:01:22,520
Let's take a look at examples for each of these seven categories to see what they mean.

18
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:28,300
By expand, I mean that you can ask a simple question such as, who is BTS?

19
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:34,320
And the chatbot will expand on that by outputting a lot of information about what you asked for.

20
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:38,340
And another way of expanding is asking it to help you generate ideas.

21
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:42,220
For example, you can ask it to give you some suggestions for jokes,

22
00:01:42,620 --> 00:01:46,760
or suggestions for places to go on vacation based on your personal interests.

23
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,680
So expand isn't a formal scientific definition,

24
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,040
but I use it to describe instances where you can give it a short prompt,

25
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:56,180
and the chatbot then outputs several paragraphs of information

26
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,040
or a list of suggestions for you to choose from.

27
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:01,060
So it's kind of expanding on your prompt.

28
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:03,440
Here's an example of asking for information.

29
00:02:03,860 --> 00:02:08,759
You can ask it, what's the difference between a golden retriever and a labrador retriever?

30
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:12,500
And you can see that it lists out differences based on different categories

31
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:15,380
like personality, health, and grooming.

32
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:18,080
And by the way, in natural language processing,

33
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:24,480
This type of task is called question answering because you ask it a question and it tries to

34
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:29,360
answer that question. And here's an example of generating ideas. I'll ask it to suggest some

35
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:34,260
jokes about puppies. And I thought this was pretty good. Why was the puppy so good at school?

36
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:41,420
Because it was the teacher's pet. Another category is synthesize. For example, you can say summarize

37
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:47,139
this and then paste in the text of an article or some paper that you're reading. Another synthesized

38
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:53,700
task is to label text. Say you have many small pieces of text, like replies to a social media

39
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:59,520
post or a couple of online customer reviews of a product. You can ask a chatbot to label them by

40
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:06,140
topic or label them as having a positive or negative sentiment. And again, synthesize isn't

41
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:12,319
an official scientific term, but I'm using it in contrast to the expand task to describe scenarios

42
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:18,100
where you feed in a lot of information into the prompt, such as an article or several social media

43
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:25,300
posts, and ask the chatbot to distill or synthesize that information into something smaller and more

44
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:31,620
digestible. So here's an example of asking a chatbot to summarize an article about Labrador retrievers.

45
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:45,420
And here's an example of the other synthesized task, labeling.

46
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:50,480
You can ask it to give topic labels to the following three articles about Paris.

47
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:08,440
The next category is Transform.

48
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:14,840
For example, you can translate from one language to another language, which is the machine translation

49
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:21,620
task that you saw earlier. And you can also reword or revise a piece of text. Let's see what that

50
00:04:21,799 --> 00:04:26,660
means. Here's an example where you can translate a phrase, every cloud has a silver lining,

51
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:35,160
from English into multiple languages at the same time. Pretty cool, eh? And here's an example of a

52
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:42,279
rewrite task. You can ask a chatbot to rewrite an article to use simple vocabulary that most people

