00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:48,860
can understand. So here's an article about corgis which uses big words and the chatbot rewrites or

54
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:56,060
transforms it using more commonly used vocabulary words. Another category of tasks is evaluate. For

55
00:04:56,200 --> 00:05:01,760
example, you can evaluate if a statement is factually correct or evaluate an essay by giving

56
00:05:01,940 --> 00:05:07,360
it a qualitative score. Here's an example of an evaluate task, fact checking. So I'm asking,

57
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:14,380
Is this an accurate statement? Since we only use 10% of our brains, only 10% of me was saying that

58
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:20,300
corgis are cuter than bulldogs. And the chatbot replies that actually we use much more than 10%

59
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:25,540
of our brains and that is a common misconception that we only use 10% of our brains. It doesn't

60
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:30,200
have any comments on whether it's correct to say that corgis are cuter than bulldogs.

61
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:36,059
I do want to mention early on that fact-checking goes both ways. You can have a chatbot help you

62
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:41,380
to fact check what humans say or write, and it's also very important for you as a human to check

63
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:46,380
what a chatbot outputs. You'll learn more about why later on in this course. Here's the other type

