It asks me some follow-ups on what is the event title and what is the time and date of the event.

85
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,440
And you can see that it added this event to my calendar.

86
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:46,660
Here's another example of taking action where a chatbot searches the internet in order to answer my question.

87
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:55,460
So I'm asking it about upcoming meteor showers, which is an example of a current or future event that will likely require the chatbot to find this information on the internet.

88
00:07:55,780 --> 00:08:03,620
Also, a really helpful feature in this case is that it also outputs links to the websites that it searched so that you can read the original source content yourself.

89
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:14,040
And fairly recently, chatbots have also been designed so that they can take in not only text, but also take in images and text together as a combined input.

